SETUP & RUN INSTRUCTIONS

Follow these steps to install and run the application.



 STEP 1: Install Python Requirements

Make sure Python 3 is installed on your system.  
Then open a terminal and run:

    pip3 install -r requirements.txt

---

STEP 2: Install Mimic 3 (TTS Engine)

You can install Mimic 3 using either pip or Git:

Option A: Install via pip (Recommended)**

    pip3 install mycroft-mimic3-tts

Option B: Install via Git**

    git clone https://github.com/MycroftAI/mimic3.git
    cd mimic3
    pip3 install .

---

STEP 3: Start the Mimic 3 Server

Keep this server running in a separate terminal window.

- On Windows**:

      mimic3-server.exe

- On Mac/Linux**:

      mimic3-server

---

STEP 4: Run the Flask Web App

In a new terminal window (same folder as app.py), run:

    python3 app.py

---

STEP 5: Open in Browser

After the server starts, you will see a link like:

    http://127.0.0.1:5000/

Click the link or copy it into your browser to access the app.

---

 TROUBLESHOOTING NOTES:

- Make sure `mimic3-server` is added to your PATH if it's not recognized.
- On Windows, restart the terminal after installing mimic3.
- Keep both `mimic3-server` and `app.py` running during usage.

---

 You're now ready to use the application!
